PLACEHOLDER — REPLACE WITH THE FILE PROVIDED BY BANK OF GEORGIA.

When using Bank of Georgia's external Apple Pay integration, BoG provides
the validation certificate / domain-association file (it represents BoG's
merchant identifier with Apple, since BoG is doing the merchant validation
on the server side using their identity certificate).

How to populate it:
  1. Download the certificate from the link in BoG's developer documentation
     (the page with "ჩამოტვირთეთ სერტიფიკატი აქ").
  2. Replace this placeholder with the contents of the downloaded file.
     Keep the filename exactly: apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association
     (no extension, no leading whitespace, no trailing newline).
  3. Deploy so the file is reachable at:
       https://<your-domain>/.well-known/apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association
     (HTTPS, no redirects, content-type doesn't matter to Apple).
  4. Email ecommercemerchants@bog.ge with:
       - your API Public Key
       - the domain you want to host the Apple Pay button on
     They'll associate your account with the domain on their end.

Notes:
  - You'll register one entry per domain (e.g. funfinder.ge, www.funfinder.ge,
    staging.funfinder.ge). Use the same file across them.
  - Some servers block dot-prefixed paths by default — make sure /.well-known/
    is publicly reachable (CRA serves it from public/ by default; for an
    nginx/Apache reverse proxy in front, allow `location /.well-known/`).
  - Re-verification is required when BoG/Apple rotates the token (rare).
